  • Several missing characters from croscore fonts (musical symbols, mathematical characters, small capital Q) (#10)

  • Latin/IPA vertical bars design issues (#8)
  • in Arimo, áµ¼á¶¥ should be based on É© (#2)
  • changes to U+1D7B U+1DA6 U+1DA7 in Arimo and Cousine (#7)

  • jumping superscripts of different sizes and different optical weights in Arimo, Cousine and Tinos (#5)

									Noto Naskh Arabic
									v2.015
								

								
Noto Naskh Arabic v2.015 This release improves anchor placement on initial veh and lam-alif ligature.


								

									Noto Naskh Arabic UI
									v2.014
								

								
Noto Naskh Arabic UI v2.014

This release
* fixes U+06F7 to prefer the Persian form and localize to the Urdu form on demand (issue #27)
* fixes some accents that were not correctly anchoring to the dotted
* brings Noto Naskh Arabic UI up to Google Fonts production standards
circle

Known Issues

								
    
									
  • Armenian kerning makes punctuation overlap diaeresis (#5)
    • 
									
  • Armenian fonts should support U+2019 RIGHT SINGLE QUOTATION MARK (#4)
    • 
									
  • Italic (cursive) variants of Georgian and Armenian (#3)
    • 
									
  • Misplaced diaeresis after Armenian digraphs (#2)
    • 
									
  • Add test cases for Armenian GPOS/GSUB? (#1)
    • 
								

							

						

					


					

						

							

								
							

						

						

							

								

									Noto Sans Armenian
									v2.007
								

								
Noto Sans Armenian v2.007

This release adds U+2024 ONE DOT LEADER (used as Armenian semicolon) to full builds of this font.


								

									Noto Serif Armenian
									v2.007
								

								
Noto Serif Armenian v2.007

This release adds U+2024 ONE DOT LEADER (used as Armenian semicolon) to full builds of this font.

  • Serif: combinations with dotted circle are bad (regr 2.001 â†’ 2.003) (#16)
    •

    •

    • 
									
  • U+1B6A BALINESE MUSICAL SYMBOL DANG GEDE overlaps the following glyph (#13)
    • 
									
  • Balinese subjoined consonants block ligatures (#12)
    • 
									
  • Balinese required ligatures use 'liga' (#11)
    • 
									
  • Incorrect rendering of some Balinese conjunct+u/uu combination  (#10)
    • 
									
  • U+1B34 BALINESE SIGN REREKAN blocks ligatures (#9)
    •

    •

    •

    • 
									
  • Various TEDUNG defects in Noto Serif Balinese Phase III (#5)

									Noto Sans Batak
									v2.002
								

								
Noto Sans Batak v2.002

This release:
* fixes a number of fontbakery fails
* moves the ligatures to the rlig feature (see #1)
* stops bindu pangolat from overlapping above/below marks (see #2)

									Noto Sans Cham
									v2.002
								

								
Noto Sans Cham v2.002

This release:
* Fixes a number of fontbakery fails
* Adds a dotless double danda as a stylistic set. (Fixes #1)
* Uses locl feature for Cham punctuation. (Fixes #2.
* Use rlig instead of liga for require features. (Fixes #3.)
* Fixes a number of mark sequence collisions which were failing to ligate.
* Adds kerning for mark sequences. (Fixes #4.)
* Reduces kerning between aa-space-ra. (Fixes #5.)

    •

    •

    • 
									
  • Inconsistent positioning of U+1193F DIVES AKURU PREFIXED NASAL SIGN (#5)
    • 
									
  • U+1193F DIVES AKURU PREFIXED NASAL SIGN and U+11941 DIVES AKURU INITIAL RA block ligatures with U+1193D DIVES AKURU SIGN HALANTA. (#4)
    • 
									
  • Many missing Dives Akuru touching conjuncts (#3)
    • 
									
  • U+11943 DIVES AKURU SIGN NUKTA blocks ligatures (#2)
    • 
								

							

						

					


					

						

							

								
							

						

						

							

								

									Noto Serif Dives Akuru
									v1.001
								

								
Noto Serif Dives Akuru v1.001

This release:

* Improves the appearance of the initial ra glyph (#8)
* Improves mark positioning and adds missing touching conjuncts (#9)
* Increases consistency by using the attached form of the prefixed nasal sign (#10)
* Renders certain ligatures as touching forms (#11)
* Avoids collisions between multiple above marks (#12)
* Uses the correct (dist) feature for spacing (#13)
* Adds the dotted circle glyph (#14)
* Removes an incorrect stylistic set (#15)
* Fixes the ligation of letter ya (#1)
* and fixes a number of fontbakery fails.

Many thanks to @sergiolmartins for all his work on this release!

Known Issues

								
    
									
  • Khmer glyph error on iOS for áž–áŸ„áŸ‡ (U+1796U+17C4U+17C7) (#9)
    • 
									
  • Overlapping pre-base U+179A KHMER LETTER RO (#8)
    • 
									
  • Khmer Consonant Shifter bugs (#7)
    • 
									
  • Noto Sans Khmer: "2 serious errors were found. Do not use these fonts." (#6)
    • 
									
  • NotoSerifKhmer variable font (NotoSerifKhmer-VF.ttf) has slightly different advance widths than that of NotoSerifKhmer phase III static font (NotoSerifKhmer-VF.ttf) (#5)
    • 
									
  • Noto Sans Khmer UI variable font & phase III static font has minor string truncation problem (#4)
    • 
									
  • some Khmer character sequences go outside UI box for Noto Sans Khmer UI (by a tiny amount) (#3)
    • 
									
  • Baseline of Noto Sans Khmer UI variable font is not aligned with Latin script (#2)
    •

Known Issues

								
    
									
  • U+1123F KHOJKI LETTER QA was disunified from U+11208 KHOJKI LETTER KA (#10)
    • 
									
  • Repha is formed in Gujarati (#9)
    • 
									
  • Trailing marks block the ká¹£a ligature (#8)
    • 
									
  • U+1123E KHOJKI SIGN SUKUN overlaps marks above (#7)
    • 
									
  • Incomplete 'salt' for U+11236 KHOJKI SIGN NUKTA (#1)
    • 
								

							

						

					


					

						

							

								
							

						

						

							

								

									Noto Sans Khojki
									v2.003
								

								
Noto Sans Khojki v2.003 This release fixes a bug whereby certain consonants before YA would be erroneously deleted.


								

									Noto Serif Khojki
									v2.002
								

								
Noto Serif Khojki v2.002

This release:
* fixes a number of fontbakery fails
* removes the unnecessary (and wrong) PUNCTUATION SPACE glyph (#3)
* removes the erroneous GUJARATI VOWEL SIGN VOCALIC R and encodes the (proposed) U+11241 KHOJKI VOWEL SIGN VOCALIC R (#4)
* fixes overlapping above vowel marks (#5)

Noto Syriac

				
    
					
  • 
						Development builds
						
					
    • 
					
  • Source repository
    • 
					
  • 
						Report a bug in this font
					
    • 
				


				

					

						

							

								
							

						

						

							

								
Known Issues

								
    
									
  • Assyrian Syriac fonts need to be broken up - the merged font set is unusable in most situations (#13)
    • 
									
  • Missing U+1DF8 and U+1DFA in Noto Sans Syriac (#12)
    • 
									
  • Malayalam Syriac is missing (#11)
    • 
									
  • Assyrian Syriac fonts not found (#10)
    • 
									
  • U+2044 FRACTION SLASH in Noto Sans Syriac (#9)
    • 
									
  • Syriac syame separates from dot over RA when vowel diacritic is used below (#8)
    • 
									
  • NotoSansSyriacEstrangela Vowel U+0735 (Zqapa) does not correctly join letter U+0720 (Lamad) (#7)
    • 
									
  • Syriac Estrangelo: confusable letter U+0724 (FINAL SEMKATH) confused with U+0723 (SEMKATH) (#6)
    • 
									
  • Overlapping Syriac glyphs (#5)
    • 
									
  • Wrong 'med2' glyph for U+0710 SYRIAC LETTER ALAPH (#4)
    • 
									
  • Nominal glyph  for U+0740 (Syriac Feminine Dot) is too close to the baseline and can be confused for full-stop (#3)
    • 
									
  • Syriac fonts should improve ligatures (#2)
    • 
									
  • Syriac: Stylistic sets defined with broken name table references (#1)
    •

									Noto Sans Tagalog
									v2.001
								

								
Noto Sans Tagalog v2.001

This release:
* Adds support for new glyphs in Unicode 14 (U+170D, U+1715, U+171F); thanks to @Mercury13 (#1, #4)
* Increases the size of the virama glyph (#2)
* Allows multiple marks to be applied without overlapping (#1)
* and fixes a number of fontbakery fails

    •

  • Telugu Noto sans and serif consonant conjuncts and vowel sign rendering issue (#8)
    • 
									
  • The base line for noto sans Telugu is not in line with English and punctuation marks.  (#1)

Noto Thai

				
    
					
  • 
						Development builds
						
					
    • 
					
  • Source repository
    • 
					
  • 
						Report a bug in this font
					
    • 
				


				

					

						

							

								
							

						

						

							

								
Known Issues

								
    
									
  • Rename Looped Thai to Sans Thai Looped (#22)
    • 
									
  • Italic and/or oblique font style (#11)
    • 
									
  • Looped Thai won't build as a variable font (#10)
    • 
									
  • Noto Sans Thai: U+F700 and U+F70F are missing (#9)
    • 
									
  • Missing substitution rule for uni0E2C loChula-thai (#7)
    • 
									
  • No contextual variants of U+0331 in Thai (#6)
    • 
									
  • Misplaced U+0331 COMBINING MACRON BELOW in Thai (#5)
    • 
									
  • Missing contextual form of U+0E0D THAI CHARACTER YO YING (#4)
    • 
									
  • U+0E4D THAI CHARACTER NIKHAHIT is reordered below tone marks (#3)
    • 
									
  • NotoSansThaiUI-ttf phase III font's stacked diacritics seems more compressed than the NotoSansThaiUI-VH.ttf's ones (#2)
    • 
									
  • some Thai character sequences go outside UI box for Noto Sans Thai UI and they shouldn't (#1)
    • 
								

							

						

					


					

						

							

								
							

						

						

							

								

									Noto Looped Thai
									v1.001
								

								
Noto Looped Thai v1.001

This is an administrative release, to fix fontbakery fails:

* The Extrabold instance has been renamed to ExtraBold
* Underline thickness has been set to constant across the family


								

									Noto Sans Thai
									v2.001
								

								
Noto Sans Thai v2.001

This is an administrative release.


								

									Noto Sans Thai Looped
									v1.001
								

								
Noto Sans Thai Looped v1.001

This is an administrative release; it renames the font from
"Noto Looped Thai" to "Noto Sans Thai Looped" and additionally fixes
some fontbakery fails:

* The Extrabold instance has been renamed to ExtraBold
* Underline thickness has been set to constant across the family


								

									Noto Serif Thai
									v2.001
								

								
Noto Serif Thai v2.001

This is an administrative release.

    • 
									
  • Noto Serif Tibetan deletes U+25CC DOTTED CIRCLE in certain contexts (#21)
    • 
									
  • Dependent vowel signs in Noto Serif Tibetan are misaligned (#20)
    • 
									
  • Excessive compression in âŸ¨à½¨à½¼à½¾âŸ© (#18)

    • 
									
  • Inconsistent contextualization of Tibetan vowel signs above tsa â€™phru (#8)

    •

    • 
									
  • Tifinagh: some ligatures seem erroneous (#7)
    • 
									
  • Wrong glyph for U+02C7 CARON in Tifinagh (#6)
    • 
									
  • NotoSansTifinagh is graphically a Neo-Tifinagh font, but uses traditional Tifinagh shaping (#5)
    • 
									
  • Bad combination of dot and macron in Tifinagh (#4)
